So far we've been trying to put the mmdb files in : 

/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/ingest-geoip ( as per the doc )
/usr/share/elasticsearch
/etc/elasticsearch/config/ingest-geoip
/etc/elasticsearch

We've also been trying a mysterious settings mention in the code : https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/7.1/modules/ingest-geoip/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/ingest/geoip/IngestGeoIpPlugin.java#L90 which is not recognized by the nodes ...

So far no luck in using other db than the provided ones.

**Elasticsearch version** (`bin/elasticsearch --version`):
6.8.0

**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:

Follow the [guide](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/client/java-rest/6.8/java-rest-high-snapshot-create-repository.html) and finally set verify false like below

```java
request.verify(false);
```

It didn't work and still throw exception（failed to create blob container）

**Steps to reproduce**:

I check the source code org.elasticsearch.client.RequestConverters and maybe find the reason.

When org.elasticsearch.client.SnapshotRequestConverters's createRepository calling withVerify, it should append verify=fasle to param but the code do nothing

```java
Params withVerify(boolean verify) {
    if (verify) {
        return putParam("verify", Boolean.TRUE.toString());
    }
    return this;
}
```

Should modify like below

```java
Params withVerify(boolean verify) {
    if (verify) {
        return putParam("verify", Boolean.TRUE.toString());
    } else {
        return putParam("verify", Boolean.FALSE.toString());
    }
}
```

